<h1>Topic 4: Tissue Level of Organization Quiz</h1>

<!-- Question 1 -->
<div class="question-container">
    <p class="question">1. Which of the following is NOT a major type of tissue?</p>
    <ul>
        <li>A) Muscular</li>
        <li>B) Nervous</li>
        <li>C) Cartilaginous</li>
        <li>D) Connective</li>
    </ul>
    <button class="show-answer" onclick="toggleAnswer(1)">Show Answer</button>
    <div id="answer1" class="answer">Answer: C) Cartilaginous<br><strong>Explanation:</strong> Cartilage is a type of connective tissue, not a primary tissue type. The four primary tissues are epithelial, connective, muscular, and nervous.</div>
</div>

<!-- Question 2 -->
<div class="question-container">
    <p class="question">2. True or False: Epithelial tissue is avascular.</p>
    <ul>
        <li>A) True</li>
        <li>B) False</li>
    </ul>
    <button class="show-answer" onclick="toggleAnswer(2)">Show Answer</button>
    <div id="answer2" class="answer">Answer: A) True<br><strong>Explanation:</strong> Epithelial tissue lacks blood vessels and relies on diffusion from underlying tissues for nutrients.</div>
</div>

<!-- Question 3 -->
<div class="question-container">
    <p class="question">3. Which connective tissue provides flexible support in the external ear?</p>
    <ul>
        <li>A) Hyaline Cartilage</li>
        <li>B) Elastic Cartilage</li>
        <li>C) Fibrocartilage</li>
        <li>D) Dense Regular Connective Tissue</li>
    </ul>
    <button class="show-answer" onclick="toggleAnswer(3)">Show Answer</button>
    <div id="answer3" class="answer">Answer: B) Elastic Cartilage<br><strong>Explanation:</strong> Elastic cartilage provides flexibility and maintains the shape of structures like the external ear and epiglottis.</div>
</div>

<!-- Question 4 -->
<div class="question-container">
    <p class="question">4. Which of the following are functions of connective tissue? (Select all that apply)</p>
    <ul>
        <li>A) Protection</li>
        <li>B) Energy Storage</li>
        <li>C) Absorption</li>
        <li>D) Support</li>
    </ul>
    <button class="show-answer" onclick="toggleAnswer(4)">Show Answer</button>
    <div id="answer4" class="answer">Answer: A, B, D<br><strong>Explanation:</strong> Connective tissue provides protection (e.g., bone), stores energy (e.g., adipose tissue), and offers structural support (e.g., cartilage and bone).</div>
</div>

<!-- Question 5 -->
<div class="question-container">
    <p class="question">5. True or False: Skeletal muscle is striated and under voluntary control.</p>
    <ul>
        <li>A) True</li>
        <li>B) False</li>
    </ul>
    <button class="show-answer" onclick="toggleAnswer(5)">Show Answer</button>
    <div id="answer5" class="answer">Answer: A) True<br><strong>Explanation:</strong> Skeletal muscle is striated and contracts under conscious control to produce movement.</div>
</div>

<!-- Question 6 -->
<div class="question-container">
    <p class="question">6. What is the main function of nervous tissue?</p>
    <ul>
        <li>A) Providing structural support</li>
        <li>B) Conducting electrical impulses</li>
        <li>C) Storing energy</li>
        <li>D) Absorbing nutrients</li>
    </ul>
    <button class="show-answer" onclick="toggleAnswer(6)">Show Answer</button>
    <div id="answer6" class="answer">Answer: B) Conducting electrical impulses<br><strong>Explanation:</strong> Nervous tissue consists of neurons that generate and transmit electrical signals to control bodily functions.</div>
</div>

<!-- Question 7 -->
<div class="question-container">
    <p class="question">7. True or False: Cardiac muscle is striated and contracts voluntarily.</p>
    <ul>
        <li>A) True</li>
        <li>B) False</li>
    </ul>
    <button class="show-answer" onclick="toggleAnswer(7)">Show Answer</button>
    <div id="answer7" class="answer">Answer: B) False<br><strong>Explanation:</strong> Cardiac muscle is striated but contracts involuntarily, as it is controlled by the autonomic nervous system.</div>
</div>

<!-- Question 8 -->
<div class="question-container">
    <p class="question">8. Which type of epithelial tissue is best suited for rapid diffusion and filtration?</p>
    <ul>
        <li>A) Simple Squamous</li>
        <li>B) Stratified Squamous</li>
        <li>C) Simple Cuboidal</li>
        <li>D) Transitional</li>
    </ul>
    <button class="show-answer" onclick="toggleAnswer(8)">Show Answer</button>
    <div id="answer8" class="answer">Answer: A) Simple Squamous<br><strong>Explanation:</strong> Simple squamous epithelium is thin, making it ideal for rapid diffusion and filtration, such as in the alveoli of the lungs.</div>
</div>

<!-- Question 9 -->
<div class="question-container">
    <p class="question">9. Which of the following are characteristics of connective tissue? (Select all that apply)</p>
    <ul>
        <li>A) Contains extracellular matrix</li>
        <li>B) Avascular</li>
        <li>C) Provides structural support</li>
        <li>D) High regeneration capacity</li>
    </ul>
    <button class="show-answer" onclick="toggleAnswer(9)">Show Answer</button>
    <div id="answer9" class="answer">Answer: A, C<br><strong>Explanation:</strong> Connective tissue has an extracellular matrix and provides structural support. It may or may not be vascular, and its regenerative capacity varies.</div>
</div>

<!-- Question 10 -->
<div class="question-container">
    <p class="question">10. True or False: Smooth muscle lacks striations and is found in the walls of hollow organs.</p>
    <ul>
        <li>A) True</li>
        <li>B) False</li>
    </ul>
    <button class="show-answer" onclick="toggleAnswer(10)">Show Answer</button>
    <div id="answer10" class="answer">Answer: A) True<br><strong>Explanation:</strong> Smooth muscle is non-striated and contracts involuntarily to control movements in hollow organs like the stomach and intestines.</div>
</div>

<!-- Question 11 -->
<div class="question-container">
    <p class="question">11. Which connective tissue type stores energy and provides insulation?</p>
    <ul>
        <li>A) Loose Areolar</li>
        <li>B) Adipose Tissue</li>
        <li>C) Dense Regular</li>
        <li>D) Fibrocartilage</li>
    </ul>
    <button class="show-answer" onclick="toggleAnswer(11)">Show Answer</button>
    <div id="answer11" class="answer">Answer: B) Adipose Tissue<br><strong>Explanation:</strong> Adipose tissue stores fat for energy, provides insulation, and cushions organs.</div>
</div>

<!-- Question 12 -->
<div class="question-container">
    <p class="question">12. Which of the following are functions of epithelial tissue? (Select all that apply)</p>
    <ul>
        <li>A) Protection</li>
        <li>B) Absorption</li>
        <li>C) Secretion</li>
        <li>D) Conducting electrical impulses</li>
    </ul>
    <button class="show-answer" onclick="toggleAnswer(12)">Show Answer</button>
    <div id="answer12" class="answer">Answer: A, B, C<br><strong>Explanation:</strong> Epithelial tissue serves functions such as protection, absorption, and secretion. Conducting electrical impulses is a function of nervous tissue.</div>
</div>

<!-- Question 13 -->
<div class="question-container">
    <p class="question">13. True or False: Cartilage is a vascular connective tissue.</p>
    <ul>
        <li>A) True</li>
        <li>B) False</li>
    </ul>
    <button class="show-answer" onclick="toggleAnswer(13)">Show Answer</button>
    <div id="answer13" class="answer">Answer: B) False<br><strong>Explanation:</strong> Cartilage is avascular, meaning it lacks blood vessels and receives nutrients through diffusion.</div>
</div>

<!-- Question 14 -->
<div class="question-container">
    <p class="question">14. Which type of connective tissue forms the intervertebral discs?</p>
    <ul>
        <li>A) Hyaline Cartilage</li>
        <li>B) Elastic Cartilage</li>
        <li>C) Fibrocartilage</li>
        <li>D) Loose Areolar</li>
    </ul>
    <button class="show-answer" onclick="toggleAnswer(14)">Show Answer</button>
    <div id="answer14" class="answer">Answer: C) Fibrocartilage<br><strong>Explanation:</strong> Fibrocartilage provides strong support and absorbs compressive forces in intervertebral discs.</div>
</div>

<!-- Question 15 -->
<div class="question-container">
    <p class="question">15. Which tissue type contains goblet cells that secrete mucus?</p>
    <ul>
        <li>A) Simple Cuboidal Epithelium</li>
        <li>B) Pseudostratified Columnar Epithelium</li>
        <li>C) Simple Squamous Epithelium</li>
        <li>D) Transitional Epithelium</li>
    </ul>
    <button class="show-answer" onclick="toggleAnswer(15)">Show Answer</button>
    <div id="answer15" class="answer">Answer: B) Pseudostratified Columnar Epithelium<br><strong>Explanation:</strong> Pseudostratified columnar epithelium often contains goblet cells that secrete mucus to trap particles and protect surfaces.</div>
</div>

